title: Taiwan Core Consumer Prices
description: Core Consumer Prices in Taiwan increased to 108.16 points in October from 107.53 points in September of 2022. Core Consumer Prices in Taiwan averaged 84.62 points from 1981 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 108.16 points in October of 2022 and a record low of 58.64 points in January of 1981. This page provides the latest reported value for - Taiwan Core Consumer Prices - plus previous releases, historical high and low, short-term forecast and long-term prediction, economic calendar, survey consensus and news.
author: DGBAS, Taiwan
